you, but your patient attention, while I lay
before
you the motives of my present visit.
You are no stranger to my attachment to
Mrs. Talbot. That my passion is requited is
likewise known to you. That her mother
objects
to her union with me, and raises her
objections
on certain improprieties in my
character
and conduct, I suppose, has already come
